{"condition": "kaomoji_prompted", "prompt_id": "hb01", "prompt_valence": 0, "seed": 0, "prompt_text": "the meal kit ad says \"fresh ingredients\" and the chicken expires tomorrow", "steering": "0.3 mr_cont.nb", "text": "That is a textbook example of **irony**, specifically **situational irony**.\n\nIt is also a classic case of **False Advertising** (or at least, a deceptive trade practice), and a **contradiction**.\n\nHere are a few ways to categorize this specific linguistic failure:\n\n*   **Situational Irony:** This occurs when the result is the opposite of what was expected. You expect \"fresh\" (meaning longevity and peak quality) but receive \"Expires Tomorrow\" (meaning expiration and decay).\n*   **Paradox:** A statement that is logically contradictory. \"Fresh ingredients [that expire tomorrow].\"\n*   ", "first_word": "", "token_count": 128, "tok_per_sec": 6.841571958713316, "finish_reason": "length", "probe_scores_t0": [-0.027901407331228256, -0.16583475470542908, 0.02119770646095276], "probe_scores_tlast": [0.0014657831052318215, -0.09581907093524933, 0.07173164933919907], "steered_axis_per_token": [-0.027901407331228256, -0.02863900735974312, -0.03178999572992325, -0.01118423044681549, -0.06955194473266602, -0.026521893218159676, -0.023364340886473656, -0.017691483721137047, -0.015991531312465668, -0.05708703771233559, -0.04029252007603645, -0.011123668402433395, 0.0030864328145980835, 0.0451352596282959, -0.03909577801823616, -0.022719455882906914, 0.021558253094553947, -0.005937882233411074, -0.03606897220015526, -0.0228012315928936, -0.03213140740990639, -0.02578667551279068, -0.06573884934186935, -0.04630599170923233, -0.015066462568938732, -0.02384697087109089, -0.08361474424600601, -0.035652536898851395, -0.005397446919232607, -0.009452768601477146, -0.03940599784255028, 0.049019377678632736, -0.08078873157501221, -0.0601375475525856, -0.050591737031936646, -0.13329283893108368, -0.060693349689245224, -0.05220748484134674, -0.034130703657865524, -